{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "O God, Be Not Silent"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "O God, be not silent; be not speechless; [^185] be not still, O God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "See how Your enemies rage, how Your foes have reared their heads."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "With cunning they scheme against Your people and conspire against those You cherish,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "saying,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Come, let us erase them as a nation; may the name of Israel be remembered no more.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For with one mind they plot together, they form an alliance against You—"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "the tents of Edom and the Ishmaelites, of Moab and the Hagrites,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "of Gebal, Ammon, and Amalek, of Philistia with the people of Tyre."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Even Assyria has joined them, lending strength to the sons of Lot. Selah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Do to them as You did to Midian, as to Sisera and Jabin at the River Kishon,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "who perished at Endor and became like dung on the ground."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Make their nobles like Oreb and Zeeb, and all their princes like Zebah and Zalmunna,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "who said,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Let us possess for ourselvesthe pastures of God.",
          "speaker": "who"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Make them like tumbleweed, O my God, like chaff before the wind."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "As fire consumes a forest, as a flame sets the mountains ablaze,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "so pursue them with Your tempest, and terrify them with Your storm."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Cover their faces with shame, that they may seek Your name, O LORD."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "May they be ever ashamed and terrified; may they perish in disgrace."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "May they know that You alone, whose name is the LORD,\nare Most High over all the earth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}